&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and highly motivated junior nurses to come and join the team based on the Ambulatory Emergency Care Unit at Ealing Hospital. Opened in 2015 we currently see around 20-30 patients per day. Our service aims to provide same day emergency care for those patients attending with undifferentiated medical conditions thereby reducing hospital admissions and reducing the pressure on the Emergency Department. We have recently moved into a new department and are currently in the process of expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for nurses who are able to work in a fast paced environment and enjoy being part of a larger multi-disciplinary team. You will need to display excellent communication skills and be able to deliver high quality care. You will be supported on shifts by the advanced clinical practitioner team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our shift patterns consist of long days (08:00-20:30. There are no night shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a supportive atmosphere as well as access to training and educational opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
